**\# ğŸ§  Brain Tumor Detection Web App**

A web-based application for detecting brain tumors in MRI scans using an ensemble of two deep learning models: a custom CNN and a fine-tuned MobileNet. The app also provides Grad-CAM visualizations to highlight regions of interest in the scan.

\- ğŸ“¤ Upload brain MRI scans (\`.jpg\`, \`.jpeg\`, \`.png\`)

\- ğŸ¯ Shows model-wise confidence scores  
\- ğŸ–¼ï¸ Generates \*\*Grad-CAM heatmap\*\* highlighting tumor regions  
\- âš™ï¸ Adjustable ensemble weights and prediction threshold  
\- ğŸ§ª MRI image validation check based on color-channel consistency

\#\# ğŸ§  Models Used

| Model        | Input Size | Description                        |  
|--------------|------------|------------------------------------|  
| \`best\_cnn.keras\` | 400x400     | Custom CNN trained on brain MRI data |  
| \`best\_mobilenet.keras\` | 224x224     | Transfer learning using MobileNet      |

Both models are trained for \*\*binary classification\*\*: \`Tumor\` vs \`No Tumor\`.
